## Plan

**Approach:**
Add a CORE corpus-source seam to internal/bench that yields plan-round "fixtures"
for the gate bench, and ship the run-refs implementation of it. Core stays
decoupled from beads/Dolt: it defines the interface + a registration seam (mirror
of the existing replay.Runner / `--runner` / `git config etude.runner` adapter
pattern) and a future beads/Dolt adapter plugs in WITHOUT core importing it.

1. CorpusSource interface (new internal/bench/corpus.go), e.g.:
     type CorpusSource interface {
         Fixtures(ctx, sel CohortSelector) ([]Fixture, error)
     }
   - Fixture = { Artifact []byte (the plan text), MediaType string,
     Provenance{ RunID, Phase, Round, SourceCommit, Stage }, Label LabelHint }.
   - LabelHint is an OPTIONAL weak hint carried from what the source can see
     (run-refs: gate status per round — rerun=had-issues, pass=clean; plus seat
     verdicts + required-change counts). It is a HINT only; real scoring/labels
     are aul.3. Keep the type minimal (e.g. GateStatus + per-seat verdict summary),
     no scoring logic here.
   - CohortSelector reuses the existing selection inputs (stage/phase name + last N).
     The corpus source COMPOSES with cohort selection rather than duplicating it:
     the run-refs source calls SelectCohort(stage="plan") to pick eligible runs,
     then reads the plan artifact + plan GateAttempts from each selected run.

2. Core run-refs source (new internal/bench/corpus_runrefs.go):
     type RunRefsSource struct { Store refstore.Store }
   - Implements CorpusSource by: SelectCohort over refs/etude/runs/* for the phase
     stage; for each CohortRun read the output artifact bytes via
     Store.ReadCommitFile(commit, stage.Output.Path); harvest the phase's
     GateAttempts (runmanifest.Gates filtered by Phase) for round + status + seat
     verdicts as the LabelHint. No beads, no Dolt, no SQLite-index dependency
     (cohort already reads manifests directly; keep that path).
   - HONEST LIMITATION (state plainly, do not paper over): the run ref holds ONE
     plan artifact per run (the final/captured plan), because dogfood capture
     OVERWRITES the plan stage. Verified on refs/etude/runs/etude-2bm.1: manifest
     has a single `plan` stage but FOUR plan gate rounds (3 rerun + 1 pass, each
     with opus/codex seat verdicts + required counts). So RunRefsSource yields, per
     run: ONE plan-text fixture, annotated with the multi-round GATE progression
     as label hints. It does NOT reconstruct the per-round plan TEXT — that rich
     multi-round plan-text corpus comes from the SEPARATE beads/Dolt adapter
     (dolt_history_issues), which is its own bead and which core must not import.

3. Registration seam (mirror replay.Runner): CorpusSource is an interface in core;
   the run-refs source is the built-in default. A future beads adapter satisfies
   CorpusSource in its own package and is selected at the CLI/config boundary
   (aul.4), exactly like ExecRunner is chosen from --runner / git config
   etude.runner in internal/cli/bench.go resolveRunner. Core defines ONLY the
   interface + the run-refs default; it does not name or import any beads adapter.

**Files:**
- internal/bench/corpus.go - new: CorpusSource interface, Fixture, Provenance,
  LabelHint, CohortSelector types. Pure contract, no I/O.
- internal/bench/corpus_runrefs.go - new: RunRefsSource implementing CorpusSource
  over refstore.Store, composing SelectCohort + ReadCommitFile + GateAttempt harvest.
- internal/bench/corpus_test.go / corpus_runrefs_test.go - new: tests.
- (No CLI/index/runmanifest changes in this bead. cohort.go reused as-is; if a
  small accessor is needed to map a CohortSelector onto SelectCohort args, add it
  in corpus_runrefs.go, not by editing cohort.go.)

**Tests:**
- RunRefsSource.Fixtures against a synthetic in-repo refstore (mirror the
  refstore/cohort test harness): build runs with a `plan` stage + multiple plan
  GateAttempts, assert one Fixture per eligible run, correct artifact bytes,
  provenance (RunID/Phase/Stage/SourceCommit), and a LabelHint that reflects the
  final gate status + per-round seat verdicts.
- Edge cases: run with no plan stage (skipped via SelectCohort), run with a plan
  stage but no plan gates (Fixture with empty/neutral LabelHint), pointer-output
  plan (skipped, mirrors existing SkipPointerOutput), ambiguous stage.
- Fixture against the REAL captured run refs/etude/runs/etude-2bm.1: assert exactly
  ONE plan fixture is produced and that its LabelHint surfaces the 4-round
  progression (3 rerun -> 1 pass) — locking in the documented one-plan-per-run
  limitation as an explicit test, not a surprise.
- Interface-level: a tiny fake CorpusSource to prove the seam is satisfiable by a
  non-core implementation (stands in for the future beads adapter) without core
  importing it.

**Docs:**
- None user-facing in this bead (internal package, no CLI yet). Add a package-doc
  comment on corpus.go stating the decoupling contract and the one-plan-per-run
  limitation. User-facing `etude bench --gate` docs land with the CLI in aul.4.

**Risks:**
- Decoupling trap: core must NOT import a beads/Dolt adapter. Mitigated by keeping
  CorpusSource a pure interface and selecting adapters at the CLI boundary (aul.4),
  mirroring resolveRunner. Verified the existing seam in internal/cli/bench.go.
- One-plan-per-run limitation is real and load-bearing: verified empirically on
  refs/etude/runs/etude-2bm.1 (1 plan stage, 4 plan gate rounds). Core yields the
  final plan + gate progression hints only; multi-round plan TEXT is the beads
  adapter's job (separate bead). Stated plainly above and pinned by a test.
- Reuse vs duplication of cohort selection: compose with SelectCohort, do not
  reimplement eligibility. Keep label/scoring logic OUT (that is aul.3); LabelHint
  is a passthrough of observable gate facts only.

